usage:

  vp [--format={ascii,binary}] [--npoints=<integer>] [--nrows=<integer>] [--ncols=<integer>] < datafile

  --format=ascii (default)
    ascii, with header line
    first line contains attribute names, whitespace delimited
    additional lines each contain all numeric attribute values for one sample, whitespace delimited

  --format=binary
    one line of ascii attribute names, whitespace delimited, ending with newline (\n);
    immediately followed by raw table of binary floating point values

  --npoints=<integer>
    number of points (samples, or rows) to read.  Default is all.

  --nrows=<integer>
    number of rows of scatterplots, default is 2.

  --ncols=<integer>
    number of columns of scatterplots, default is 2.

Keys & Buttons (in plot windows):

action			key
------			----
new selection		left-mouse
move selection		left-mouse + right-shift
continue selction	left-mouse + left-shift
invert selection	i
display deselected 	d
remove selected points	x (or delete)

translate		right-mouse
scale			middle-mouse
scale histogram		middle-mouse + h
reset view		r
quit			q


Controls in control panels:

control		action
------		------
npoints		number of points displayed




